OL,3,C'Not justified': Thousands of
OL,4,Cgovernment credit cards to be cancelled
OL,6,FOver the past four years the amount
OL,7,Fspent on government credit cards has
OL,8,Fmore than quadrupled, with spending in
OL,9,Fthe last financial year reaching over
OL,10,F#600 million in central departments
OL,11,Fand core agencies.
OL,13,FTighter new spending controls are also
OL,14,Fset to be introduced, with the maximum
OL,15,Fspend for hospitality slashed from
OL,16,F#2,500 to #500, and any spend over
OL,17,F#500 requiring Director General
OL,18,Fapproval.
